    "summary": "Marleen Spierings is a poet, a learner-teacher, and an innovator within the Dutch Curriculum of English language & culture, science communication & global citizenship. She researches knowledge creation within CEFR CLIL curricular development within education as ecological systems and disarmed positive pedagogies and how these can reorganise educational experiences and curricular design practice in Shared Cultural Heritage: \"If the digital future is to be our home, then it is we who must make it\" (Zuboff, 2014) in a \"spirit of dialogue, [and] the ability to hold many points of view in suspension, along with a primary interest in the creation of common meaning'' (Bohm, 1987).  Also, \"the rhizome pertains to a map that must be produced, constructed, a map that is always detachable, connectible, reversible, modifiable, and has multiple entryways and exits and its own lines of flight\" (Deleuze and Guattari 1987, 21), such are learning and teaching experiences in a wider school context. Spierings started working on a didactic and pedagogical node-vector principle within a 4D Rhizomatic Model for Language and Cultural Learning to enhance ESL classrooms and promote dynamic language acquisition and intercultural competence within a CEFR-based Dynamic Pluri-Cultural Literacies Curriculum in 2014. Our Co-Labs curate educational content: https://sociating.com/erfgoed-wijsheid-cultural-heritage-learning/, https://sociating.com/tech-ethics-teachers/, https://www.analyticalpha.nl, https://www.leiden-education-alphalab.eu, https://www.challenges-leiden.eu. I am a Sociator (community manager on Sociating.com) where I work with great teachers and designers along the lines of 'The Art of Thinking Together' in a generative dialogue (Isaacs, 2008).  Sociating.com (feb. 2020) is a Dutch start-up that globally connects students (ba, ma, Phd) with experts. In that light, I venture to coordinate projects for \"De Leidse Aanpak\", a Leiden innovation network with a strong focus on developing programmes for gifted (SEN) students. Also, I connect to the LEF network: Leiden Educational Fieldlab/Hogeschool Leiden and ONZ/Onderwijs Netwerk Zuid-Hollend/University of Leiden. I coordinate and participate in Professional Learning Communities on a regional, national and international level.\n\nMy Classroom might be a  Distortion Room and a Word Smithy within which my students and I develop a Curriculum of Creative Alpha Academics & Alpha Analytics: educational innovation and technology in Critical Civic and Digital Literacy in Higher Secondary General Education Netherlands.",
